  "title": "Senior Sales Manager",
  "description": "<p>This position is accountable for the profitability enhancement, sales acquisition, client\nretention, and growth of the corporate sales portfolio. Executes the strategic sales plan to ensure realization of goals in a timely, professional and profitable manner.</p><ul><li>Meet and exceed the Room Revenue goals established for the account portfolio through\na strategic and aggressive sales solicitation of rooms and meetings business\nfrom the Corporate market.  </li><li>Within the context of the sales territory allocation, develop an appropriate Sales Plan to accomplish the established goals and objectives.  </li><li>Undertake a systematic and planned schedule of sales calls to qualify the corporate account prospects and leads in the assigned territory or industry.   </li><li>Develop a profile for each qualified account, and categorize these according to their estimated volume of business potential for the Hotel.</li><li>Develop a hit-list of volume and preferred accounts and commence the appropriate course\nof sales action, from the point when the Requests For Proposals (RFPs) are\nissued to its submission.  </li><li>Follow through with these RFPs to ensure the Hotel is listed in the corporate hotel\ndirectories and travel programs, and the rates loaded in the GDS.</li><li> Negotiate and prepare corporate agreements for the other preferred and corporate\naccounts.</li><li>Establish and maintain contact and communication with The Fullerton Singapore’s Regional and Representative offices, where available, for information and leads on\nprospective clients.</li><li>Further market penetration through segmentation of accounts.</li><li>Operate within budget.</li><li>Submit reports within pre-determined time frame.</li><li>Networks within the existing client base to attain additional revenue.</li><li>Maintains processes to ensure aged receivables remain at zero balance.</li><li>Performs any other related duties that may be assigned from time to time. </li></ul>",
